Whereas section 1672 of the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2008 ( Public Law 110–181
; 10 U.S.C. 1071 note) introduced an expansion of medical care available to family caregivers, and the
Caregivers and Veterans Omnibus Health Services Act of 2010 ( Public Law 111–163 ) facilitated a new program for access to health insurance, mental health services, caregiver training, and respite care by family caregivers of veterans who served in Operation Enduring Freedom or Operation Iraqi Freedom;
